# Day 17: Data Transformation with Functions

## What I Learned

Today I learned how to transform structured data using functions. In previous lessons, I mainly focused on reading data, filtering records, and counting results. Today was different because I started learning how to take existing data and create a completely new version of that data.

I worked with a list of dictionaries where each dictionary represented one student. Inside the function, I looped through each student, checked the student's age, and created a new dictionary with a different field based on a condition. Instead of only displaying the original data, I learned how to build a new list that contained transformed information.

This helped me understand that functions can do more than organize code. A function can also act as a reusable processor that receives raw data, applies logic, and returns cleaner or more useful data. That concept feels much closer to how real software handles information.

