## Important Insight

The most important thing I learned today is that programming is not only about reading data. It is also about changing data into a better format.

I started understanding this process:

raw data → process → transformed data

That way of thinking is important because many real systems work by receiving data, transforming it, and then sending it somewhere else.

I also started seeing that:
- lists can store multiple objects
- dictionaries can represent one object
- functions can transform those objects
- return can send the new data back

That structure feels much closer to real development.

